# Windows: project (P:) and global pnpm store (L:) on different drives causes
# path.relative → L:\... absolute path → new URL() uses "l:" protocol → Astro build fails
# with "The URL must be of scheme file". Keep store on the same drive as the project.
# See: https://pnpm.io/faq#does-pnpm-work-across-multiple-drives-or-filesystems
store-dir=.pnpm-store
package-import-method=copy
node-linker=hoisted
